"use strict";(self.webpackChunkdevraven_docs=self.webpackChunkdevraven_docs||[]).push([[1477],{10:function(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"functions","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/functions","source":"@site/blog/2022-07-20-mdx-blog-post-1.mdx","title":"Functions and PagerDuty integration","description":"Reusable functions is one of the most asked feature by our early access customers. Reusable functions help prevent duplication of code across multiple monitoring checks.","date":"2022-07-20T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"July 20, 2022","tags":[{"label":"DevRaven","permalink":"/blog/tags/dev-raven"}],"readingTime":0.77,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"Krishna Chaitanya Thota","title":"Founder","url":"https://github.com/kcthota","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2999820?v=4","key":"kc"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"functions","title":"Functions and PagerDuty integration","authors":["kc"],"tags":["DevRaven"]},"nextItem":{"title":"API Monitoring","permalink":"/blog/api-monitoring"}},"content":"Reusable functions is one of the most asked feature by our early access customers. Reusable functions help prevent duplication of code across multiple monitoring checks.\\n\\nFunctions defined in a Workspace can be invoked from Scripts in Synthetic Tests or API monitoring checks. For more details about Functions, refer the documentation [here](https://docs.devraven.io/docs/functions/overview).\\n\\nPagerDuty integration is now available. More details on [PagerDuty website](https://www.pagerduty.com/integrations/devraven/) and also refer our documentation [here](https://docs.devraven.io/docs/integrations/pd-integration)\\n\\nNew availability of persistence APIs to write/retrieve values to temporary storage for monitoring complex dependent scenarios. Refer documentation [here](https://docs.devraven.io/docs/api-monitoring/preserving-values)\\n\\nAs we get closer to public availability of the product, we also integrated with Stripe for subscription management and billing. We also clarified our [Pricing](https://www.devraven.io/pricing.html) details on our public website.\\n\\nFew other updates include:\\n\\n* Changes to Home screen to show usage details\\n* Changes to Home screen to show TODO items.\\n* Documented publicly available APIs in [API monitoring checks](https://docs.devraven.io/docs/api-monitoring/available-apis) and [Synthetic tests](https://docs.devraven.io/docs/synthetic-monitoring/available-apis)\\n* few bug fixes"},{"id":"api-monitoring","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/api-monitoring","source":"@site/blog/2022-06-20-mdx-blog-post copy.mdx","title":"API Monitoring","description":"We are excited to announce availability of API monitoring for all customers in all the available monitoring regions.","date":"2022-06-20T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 20, 2022","tags":[{"label":"DevRaven","permalink":"/blog/tags/dev-raven"}],"readingTime":0.755,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"Krishna Chaitanya Thota","title":"Founder","url":"https://github.com/kcthota","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2999820?v=4","key":"kc"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"api-monitoring","title":"API Monitoring","authors":["kc"],"tags":["DevRaven"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Functions and PagerDuty integration","permalink":"/blog/functions"},"nextItem":{"title":"Preview Release","permalink":"/blog/product-preview"}},"content":"We are excited to announce availability of API monitoring for all customers in all the available monitoring regions.\\n\\nAPI monitoring allows you to setup and monitor your critical REST end points to ensure they are working as expected. Similar to other types of monitors, you can also setup monitoring schedules to run your test at regular intervals. Currently the lowest interval we support for executing tests in all regions is 5 minutes.\\n\\nWe also updated the documentation to clarify the data retention periods for monitoring data. All preview and free plan workspaces will have a data retention period of 10 days and paid workspaces will have a default data retention period of 30 days.\\n\\nFew other updates include:\\n\\n* Manage Workspace (rename or delete Workspace)\\n* The ability to snooze or view snooze status from list view for all monitors.\\n* Support for adding tags to monitors\\n* other bug fixes"},{"id":"product-preview","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/product-preview","source":"@site/blog/2022-06-01-mdx-blog-post.mdx","title":"Preview Release","description":"Starting June 6th, 2022, DevRaven will be available as limited preview release. This release will help us gather feedback for fellow developers on the features and course correct the roadmap based on customer needs.","date":"2022-06-01T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 1, 2022","tags":[{"label":"DevRaven","permalink":"/blog/tags/dev-raven"}],"readingTime":0.545,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"Krishna Chaitanya Thota","title":"Founder","url":"https://github.com/kcthota","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2999820?v=4","key":"kc"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"product-preview","title":"Preview Release","authors":["kc"],"tags":["DevRaven"]},"prevItem":{"title":"API Monitoring","permalink":"/blog/api-monitoring"}},"content":"Starting June 6th, 2022, DevRaven will be available as limited preview release. This release will help us gather feedback for fellow developers on the features and course correct the roadmap based on customer needs.\\n\\nThe features available include:\\n\\n* Synthetic Monitoring\\n* SSL Monitoring\\n* Web Page Monitoring\\n* User Management including invite user flows.\\n* Roles\\n* Workspace Management\\n* Global alert settings\\n\\nMore features are in the works and changes get deployed everyday.\\n\\nWe hope you find DevRaven useful for your development and operations needs. If you have any questions or feedback or need a 1-1 session to help you get started, please reach out to support@devraven.io"}]}')}}]);